titleproper.value: Guide to the "William Meyers: Civics" Exhibition Photographs<lb/>2002-2016<lb/> <num>PR 394</num>

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2019-05-31T12:48:20</date>

abstract.value: Photographs exhibited in October 2016 as "William Meyers: Civics" at Nailya Alexander Gallery, New York. Through sections labeled "Politics," "Demonstrations," "Press," and "Powwows," Meyers' images explore the ways in which individual citizens involve themselves in the procedures, rituals, symbols, and rhetoric of American democracy.

p.value: Open to qualified researchers by appointment only.

This collection should be cited as: "<emph render="underline">William Meyers: Civics" exhibition photographs, PR 394, Department of Prints, Photographs, and Architectural Collections, The New-York Historical Society</emph>.
Gift of Richard S. Frary, 2016 (accession no. PPAC-2016-050).
